original: Hässler, Ivar Gustaf, distriktsveterinär, Alvesta, f. 18/2/88 i Jämshög, Blek. 1., av L. J. Pettersson o. J. M. Hässler. G. 15 m. Elsa Lizelius. Barn: Karin f. 18, Lars 21. — Mog:-ex. 08, vet:ex. 13. Distr :vet. i Alvesta distr. sed. 14, bataljonsvet. i Fvk :s res. Hed :ordf. i Alvesta isimsälilsk. Resor t. Danm. 16, Tyskl. 38. Hobby: jakt.
translated: Hässler, Ivar Gustaf, district veterinarian, Alvesta, born February 18th, 1888 in Jämshög, Blekinge County. Son of L.J. Pettersson and J.M. Hässler. Married to Elsa Lizelius in 1915 and has two children: Karin born in 1918 and Lars born in 1921. Graduated from the Veterinary Institute in 1908 and became a certified veterinarian in 1913. Worked as a district veterinarian in Alvesta since 1914 and as a battalion veterinarian in the Swedish Army Reserve. Also served as chairman of the hunting association in Alvesta. Traveled to Denmark in 1916 and Germany in 1938. Hobbies include hunting.
